            <div id="cite-apa" class="tab selected" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-0" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_apa rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_apa rendering_contributiontojournal_apa">Irfan, M., Dalai, S., Trslic, P.<a rel="Person" href="https://research-portal.uws.ac.uk/en/persons/james-riordan/" class="link"><span>, Riordan, J.</span></a>, &amp; Dooly, G. (2025). <a rel="ContributionToJournal" href="https://research-portal.uws.ac.uk/en/publications/lsaf-lstm-based-self-adaptive-multi-sensor-fusion-for-robust-uav-/" class="link"><span>LSAF-LSTM-based self-adaptive multi-sensor fusion for robust UAV state estimation in challenging environments</span></a>. <a rel="Journal" href="#" class="link"><span><em>Machines</em></span></a>, <em>13</em>(2), Article 130. <a onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank','noopener,noreferrer'); return false;" href="https://doi.org/10.3390/machines13020130" class="link"><span>https://doi.org/10.3390/machines13020130</span></a></div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-author" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-1" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_author rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_author rendering_contributiontojournal_author">Irfan, Mahammad ; Dalai, Sagar ; Trslic, Petar et al. / <a rel="ContributionToJournal" href="https://research-portal.uws.ac.uk/en/publications/lsaf-lstm-based-self-adaptive-multi-sensor-fusion-for-robust-uav-/" class="link"><span><strong>LSAF-LSTM-based self-adaptive multi-sensor fusion for robust UAV state estimation in challenging environments</strong></span></a>. In: <a rel="Journal" href="#" class="link"><span>Machines</span></a>. 2025 ; Vol. 13, No. 2.</div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-BIBTEX" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-2" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_bibtex rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_bibtex rendering_contributiontojournal_bibtex"><div>@article{1f6175446a784954b92aeea337c97386,</div><div>  title     = "LSAF-LSTM-based self-adaptive multi-sensor fusion for robust UAV state estimation in challenging environments",</div><div>  abstract  = "Unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) state estimation is fundamental across applications like robot navigation, autonomous driving, virtual reality (VR), and augmented reality (AR). This research highlights the critical role of robust state estimation in ensuring safe and efficient autonomous UAV navigation, particularly in challenging environments. We propose a deep learning-based adaptive sensor fusion framework for UAV state estimation, integrating multi-sensor data from stereo cameras, an IMU, two 3D LiDAR{\textquoteright}s, and GPS. The framework dynamically adjusts fusion weights in real time using a long short-term memory (LSTM) model, enhancing robustness under diverse conditions such as illumination changes, structureless environments, degraded GPS signals, or complete signal loss where traditional single-sensor SLAM methods often fail. Validated on an in-house integrated UAV platform and evaluated against high-precision RTK ground truth, the algorithm incorporates deep learning-predicted fusion weights into an optimization-based odometry pipeline. The system delivers robust, consistent, and accurate state estimation, outperforming state-of-the-art techniques. Experimental results demonstrate its adaptability and effectiveness across challenging scenarios, showcasing significant advancements in UAV autonomy and reliability through the synergistic integration of deep learning and sensor fusion.",</div><div>  keywords  = "ROS, LSTM, adaptive-fusion, multi-sensor fusion, state-estimation, UAV, lidar-visual-inertial odometry",</div><div>  author    = "Mahammad Irfan and Sagar Dalai and Petar Trslic and James Riordan and Gerard Dooly",</div><div>  year      = "2025",</div><div>  month     = feb,</div><div>  day       = "9",</div><div>  doi       = "10.3390/machines13020130",</div><div>  language  = "English",</div><div>  volume    = "13",</div><div>  journal   = "Machines",</div><div>  issn      = "2075-1702",</div><div>  publisher = "MDPI Multidisciplinary Digital Publishing Institute",</div><div>  number    = "2",</div><p>}</p></div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-harvard" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-3" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_harvard rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_harvard rendering_contributiontojournal_harvard">Irfan, M, Dalai, S, Trslic, P<a rel="Person" href="https://research-portal.uws.ac.uk/en/persons/james-riordan/" class="link"><span>, Riordan, J</span></a> &amp; Dooly, G 2025, '<a rel="ContributionToJournal" href="https://research-portal.uws.ac.uk/en/publications/lsaf-lstm-based-self-adaptive-multi-sensor-fusion-for-robust-uav-/" class="link harvard_title"><span>LSAF-LSTM-based self-adaptive multi-sensor fusion for robust UAV state estimation in challenging environments</span></a>', <a rel="Journal" href="#" class="link"><span><em>Machines</em></span></a>, vol. 13, no. 2, 130. <a onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank','noopener,noreferrer'); return false;" href="https://doi.org/10.3390/machines13020130" class="link"><span>https://doi.org/10.3390/machines13020130</span></a></div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-standard" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-4" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_standard rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_standard rendering_contributiontojournal_standard"><a rel="ContributionToJournal" href="https://research-portal.uws.ac.uk/en/publications/lsaf-lstm-based-self-adaptive-multi-sensor-fusion-for-robust-uav-/" class="link"><span><strong>LSAF-LSTM-based self-adaptive multi-sensor fusion for robust UAV state estimation in challenging environments.</strong></span></a> / Irfan, Mahammad; Dalai, Sagar; Trslic, Petar et al. <br />In: <a rel="Journal" href="#" class="link"><span>Machines</span></a>, Vol. 13, No. 2, 130, 09.02.2025.<p class="type"><span class="type_family">Research output<span class="type_family_sep">: </span></span><span class="type_classification_parent">Contribution to journal<span class="type_parent_sep"> › </span></span><span class="type_classification">Article</span><span class="type_classification"><span class="type_parent_sep"> › </span>peer-review</span></p></div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-RIS" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-5" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_ris rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_ris rendering_contributiontojournal_ris"><p>TY  - JOUR</p><p>T1  - LSAF-LSTM-based self-adaptive multi-sensor fusion for robust UAV state estimation in challenging environments</p><p>AU  - Irfan, Mahammad</p><p>AU  - Dalai, Sagar</p><p>AU  - Trslic, Petar </p><p>AU  - Riordan, James</p><p>AU  - Dooly, Gerard</p><p>PY  - 2025/2/9</p><p>Y1  - 2025/2/9</p><p>N2  - Unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) state estimation is fundamental across applications like robot navigation, autonomous driving, virtual reality (VR), and augmented reality (AR). This research highlights the critical role of robust state estimation in ensuring safe and efficient autonomous UAV navigation, particularly in challenging environments. We propose a deep learning-based adaptive sensor fusion framework for UAV state estimation, integrating multi-sensor data from stereo cameras, an IMU, two 3D LiDAR’s, and GPS. The framework dynamically adjusts fusion weights in real time using a long short-term memory (LSTM) model, enhancing robustness under diverse conditions such as illumination changes, structureless environments, degraded GPS signals, or complete signal loss where traditional single-sensor SLAM methods often fail. Validated on an in-house integrated UAV platform and evaluated against high-precision RTK ground truth, the algorithm incorporates deep learning-predicted fusion weights into an optimization-based odometry pipeline. The system delivers robust, consistent, and accurate state estimation, outperforming state-of-the-art techniques. Experimental results demonstrate its adaptability and effectiveness across challenging scenarios, showcasing significant advancements in UAV autonomy and reliability through the synergistic integration of deep learning and sensor fusion.</p><p>AB  - Unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) state estimation is fundamental across applications like robot navigation, autonomous driving, virtual reality (VR), and augmented reality (AR). This research highlights the critical role of robust state estimation in ensuring safe and efficient autonomous UAV navigation, particularly in challenging environments. We propose a deep learning-based adaptive sensor fusion framework for UAV state estimation, integrating multi-sensor data from stereo cameras, an IMU, two 3D LiDAR’s, and GPS. The framework dynamically adjusts fusion weights in real time using a long short-term memory (LSTM) model, enhancing robustness under diverse conditions such as illumination changes, structureless environments, degraded GPS signals, or complete signal loss where traditional single-sensor SLAM methods often fail. Validated on an in-house integrated UAV platform and evaluated against high-precision RTK ground truth, the algorithm incorporates deep learning-predicted fusion weights into an optimization-based odometry pipeline. The system delivers robust, consistent, and accurate state estimation, outperforming state-of-the-art techniques. Experimental results demonstrate its adaptability and effectiveness across challenging scenarios, showcasing significant advancements in UAV autonomy and reliability through the synergistic integration of deep learning and sensor fusion.</p><p>KW  - ROS</p><p>KW  - LSTM</p><p>KW  - adaptive-fusion</p><p>KW  - multi-sensor fusion</p><p>KW  - state-estimation</p><p>KW  - UAV</p><p>KW  - lidar-visual-inertial odometry</p><p>U2  - 10.3390/machines13020130</p><p>DO  - 10.3390/machines13020130</p><p>M3  - Article</p><p>SN  - 2075-1702</p><p>VL  - 13</p><p>JO  - Machines</p><p>JF  - Machines</p><p>IS  - 2</p><p>M1  - 130</p><p>ER  - </p></div>
            </div>
        
